00:23:04,841 --> 00:23:07,427
We're everyone's favorite distraction
from their boring lives

488
00:23:07,511 --> 00:23:09,596
-for the next five minutes.
-♪ Oh, yeah, at last… ♪

489
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:11,431
Enjoy your moment in the spotlight.

490
00:23:13,642 --> 00:23:16,478
-Are you wearing makeup?
-No! St… N…

491
00:23:16,561 --> 00:23:18,897
-What?
-Okay, fine.

492
00:23:18,980 --> 00:23:23,276
Maybe… maybe I was, you know,
trying to cover up a little of the damage

493
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:27,364
so that I would look better
seeing you again and your new boyfriend.

494
00:23:28,073 --> 00:23:32,828
Glad I got to avoid that one.
Craig notwithstanding.

495
00:23:32,911 --> 00:23:33,954
You look fine.

496
00:23:35,330 --> 00:23:37,332
My new boyfriend
would have been very jealous.

497
00:23:37,416 --> 00:23:38,708
[Michael chuckles]

498
00:23:41,378 --> 00:23:44,339
And if it's what you really want,
you can buy me out of the apartment.

499
00:23:44,423 --> 00:23:47,217
♪ That I could speak to… ♪

500
00:23:48,969 --> 00:23:52,305
-It is. Thank you.
-♪ A dream that I… ♪

501
00:23:52,389 --> 00:23:54,474
-You seem really good, you know?
-♪ Can call my own… ♪

502
00:23:54,558 --> 00:23:57,477
Different. I mean, not that you didn't
feel-- well, seem good before--

503
00:23:57,561 --> 00:23:58,728
-No, I know.
-Okay.

504
00:23:58,812 --> 00:24:00,814
-♪ A thrill… ♪
-I guess I am a little different.

505
00:24:00,897 --> 00:24:03,650
-♪ To rest my cheek to… ♪
-How could I not be?

506
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:07,988
♪ Right.
-♪ A thrill… ♪

507
00:24:08,071 --> 00:24:11,408
-Right.
-♪ I have never known… ♪

508
00:24:11,491 --> 00:24:13,952
Well, I'm gonna say my goodbyes
and head out.

509
00:24:15,245 --> 00:24:17,622
Thanks for the heads-up
that you're leaving this time.

510
00:24:18,123 --> 00:24:19,207
-[laughs]
-Right.

511
00:24:19,291 --> 00:24:22,794
-♪ Oh, and then the spell was cast… ♪
-It was nice seeing you, Michael. Really.

512
00:24:22,878 --> 00:24:23,920
-Same here.
-Yeah.

513
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:31,011
-You smell good. You always did.
-♪ And here we are… ♪

514
00:24:31,094 --> 00:24:33,889
-You take care, handsome.
-You too, handsomer.

515
00:24:36,183 --> 00:24:41,855
♪ For you are mine ♪

516
00:24:41,938 --> 00:24:46,067
♪ At last ♪

517
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:53,658
Oh, here he comes.

518
00:24:54,743 --> 00:24:57,287
[upbeat pop music playing]

519
00:24:58,371 --> 00:24:59,873
What the fuck with the dancing?

520
00:24:59,956 --> 00:25:03,418
-That was some crazy shit out there.
-Are you getting back together?

521
00:25:03,502 --> 00:25:05,504
Of course not. Are you insane?

522
00:25:05,587 --> 00:25:08,465
Well, it was nice
seeing the two of you like that.

523
00:25:08,548 --> 00:25:11,343
It was nice.
I think we can actually be friends.

524
00:25:11,426 --> 00:25:13,178
Not now, but someday.

525
00:25:13,261 --> 00:25:14,638
Really? What happened?

526
00:25:14,721 --> 00:25:18,225
I don't know.
It didn't hurt like it used to.

527
00:25:18,308 --> 00:25:21,645
It feels like the bleeding
has finally stopped.

528
00:25:21,728 --> 00:25:22,896
What about the apartment?

529
00:25:23,688 --> 00:25:24,606
He says I can stay.

530
00:25:24,689 --> 00:25:26,858
Have you tried the cake? It's gluten-free.

531
00:25:26,942 --> 00:25:27,984
-Ugh!
-Hideous!

532
00:25:28,068 --> 00:25:29,486
It's like the chicken with icing.

533
00:25:29,569 --> 00:25:32,739
-What time is the doctor on Monday?
-Noon. Billy's going too.

534
00:25:33,323 --> 00:25:35,408
Really? Cool. Hey, where's Wyatt?

535
00:25:35,492 --> 00:25:36,743
-Oh…
-Uh…

536
00:25:36,826 --> 00:25:38,328
I may have shit the bed on that one.

537
00:25:38,411 --> 00:25:41,706
I won. I want you all to pay me my money.

538
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:43,750
-Were you all taking bets?
-I don't have any dough.

539
00:25:43,833 --> 00:25:45,544
-Wait, I liked Wyatt!
-There's no bet to me.

540
00:25:45,627 --> 00:25:47,003
-I told you.
-Everybody liked Wyatt.

541
00:25:47,087 --> 00:25:48,713
So why isn't he still here?

542
00:25:48,797 --> 00:25:53,134
Because someone doesn't know
how to treat a man.

